I believe I may have found the cause of this. 

I am not a dev here so I'll just post my proposed fix for anyone to checkin or how it works here =)

Index: C:/Users/jowi/Desktop/Rawr/Rawr.Warlock/Spell.cs
===================================================================
--- C:/Users/jowi/Desktop/Rawr/Rawr.Warlock/Spell.cs	(revision 34296)
+++ C:/Users/jowi/Desktop/Rawr/Rawr.Warlock/Spell.cs	(working copy)
@@ -1060,7 +1060,7 @@
         public override void Calculate(Stats stats, Character character)
         {
                 Spell tmpImmo = new Immolate (stats, character);
-                MinDamage = MaxDamage = tmpImmo.DotDamage / (tmpImmo.DebuffDuration / tmpImmo.TimeBetweenTicks) * 15;
+                MinDamage = MaxDamage = tmpImmo.DotDamage / tmpImmo.DebuffDuration * 12;
 
1st, the nerf to Conflag was not implemented (12 instead of 15 sec worth of immolate)
2nd, you got an inflated value due to some freaky math. The total damage was calculated involving time between ticks aswell as total duration basicly ending up with that immo ticks once per second at the normal 3s damage which lead to a multiple of 3 too much damage

Side note:
I've been using Rawr for my druid @ 70 and came back today to check up on a Destro lock model, found the issue, DL the source and tried to fix it (primarily for personal use, but im happy to share). Although it seems to work, as Im quite unfamiliar with the codebase there could possibly be lots of other places changes need to go in aswell so dont count on this to be a 100% fix


